snippet.textDisplay: Hey Jaclyn — it was brave of you to post this video, and I think we can all appreciate your vulnerability, here. Thanks for that! However, please don’t make a habit of lumping in people who take prescribed antidepressants with those who self-medicate via alcohol, etc. Antidepressants can be VERY beneficial for those who deal with depression/anxiety. Some people — for example, those with family history/recurring episodes — will stay on medication for years or for life. And that’s okay! Please don’t contribute to the stigma/mythology that surrounds long-term use of antidepressants. It’s definitely damaging.

snippet.textDisplay: Wow! It’s been a minute since I’ve watched one of your videos and man, anxiety and depressions are no joke!! I went through it in 2018 and I lost 10lbs in 3 weeks cuz I couldn’t eat, I was restless all the time, I had horrible insomnia. Anyways, my point is I am so sorry you had to go through that! It is unfortunate that people can be so cruel and heartless nowadays! And the fakeness, is so unreal! I’m glad you were able to get yourself out of it and recognized the help you needed! That is one big step to recovery! As sad as it is to see negative, insensitive comments, but know there are as many real and caring people out there! Never apologize for who you are! You keep being real to yourself and continue to do what’s right! At the end of the day, you need to be able to look at yourself in the mirror and be happy and proud of yourself. You only need your own validation, not everyone else! Stay positive, stay focus and ignore the haters! Real people will understand and will love you and your products regardless of your situation. Good luck to your recovery! Stay real because that is what draw me to started watching your videos and why I started following you! #positivevibesonly

snippet.textDisplay:
I can absolutely comment on the destruction depression can wreak. I assumed in recent months that Jacyln was possibly suffering from some medical issues, & that was her business to share or not share. Prednisone & some other similar meds can cause a side effect called "moon face" that leaves swelling & retention of fluids in the jawline. It's prescribed for IBS, Crohn's & other inflammatory conditions. My aunt has Crohn's & I do not wish it on anyone, so I'm very glad she is not dealing with that. I def never believed she had just gone & gotten fillers in her cheeks because she has clearly said she did not like the swelling in her face & did not choose to have it look that way, but again, Her Business.
I'm sad that the internet is so full of body shamers & women who are so ready to tear other women down. That so many can be dense to how their words affect others is mind blowing to me. The worse side is those that know the affects their words will have & say/type them anyway, sometimes gleefully. Think before you speak, before you type.
Your opinion of Jaclyn aside, we all know most of her subscribers are a young female audience. Those young girls, young women, might read a cruel comment about weight gain & apply it to their bodies, their minds. If you put cruel & mean out into the world, they will snowball, gaining steam quickly, affecting so many in their paths. How many of us have read a bullying comment on Youtube, Instagram or FB that was directed at a complete stranger & gotten angry, felt hurt? It affects so many more people that just the directed recipient.
I have dealt with anxiety, depression & even occassional bouts of being suicidal for 14 yrs (not in recent years Thank God) & it can put you in bed for days, cause weight gain, body pain, hormonal imbalances leading to acne & migraines, etc etc. You have no interest in the things you used to love or they cause you so much anxiety at times you fear doing them. If you have having symptoms of depression that last more than 2 weeks, see a Dr., share your story. I didn't seek treatment for years & I feel as if I lost years of my life. I stayed in a fog, telling myself it was stress, a cold, hormones etc etc etc...until I couldn't make excuses anyone. I had fluctuating weight for years due to these things & people around you can be harsh, rude & callous. 1 cruel comment can place you in a state of mind that lasts for weeks, sometimes that comment follows you forever...it replays in your mind. I have a lot of confidence now as I've gotten older & wiser & become comfortable in my skin, my mind & emotions, at 35 I'm far far different than I was at 25, but I'm not immune to hurtful. No 1 is...we all need to remember that!

snippet.textDisplay: Sometimes I’m skeptical of what YouTubers say because they get paid to do what they do so sometimes you feel that they lose their sincerity with the money, but at the end of the day YouTubers are still human and should be allowed to express their opinions and say things without every little detail getting attacked. Sure, it comes with the territory and you should know that if you’re going to be a public figure that you’re going to be scrutinized. But it doesn’t  make the level of scrutiny that some people go to any better. People mess up and should be allowed to apologize and try to grow from the experience. YouTubers are human beings and should be treated as such. We spend so much time fighting each other that we forget what’s important in life. You don’t even know the YouTuber. How does it affect your personal life? It doesn’t, sorry. I won’t say I agree with everything some public figures do or say, but I will speak out for their right to live and learn.
